# Zarechye, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Zarechye () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kabansky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 335 as of 2010. There are 10 streets.
Geography
Zarechye is located 98&nbsp;km northeast of Kabansk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Sukhaya is the nearest rural locality.
